# Material UI Guidelines

- **Installation & setup:** install `@mui/material`, `@emotion/react` and `@emotion/styled`.
- **Grid usage:** emphasise that the `Grid` component uses Flexbox, not CSS Grid, so you must specify the `container` prop for wrappersmui.com (https://mui.com/material-ui/react-grid/#:~:text=How%20it%20works). Grid items do not span rows and do not auto-place children; use CSS Grid or `Stack` when row spanning or auto-placement is requiredmui.com (https://mui.com/material-ui/react-grid/#:~:text=,recommend%20using%20CSS%20Grid%20instead).
- **Breakpoints & sizing:** explain default breakpoints (`xs`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`) and the `size` prop to control column spansmui.com (https://mui.com/material-ui/react-grid/#:~:text=relative%20to%20their%20parent%20element,recommend%20using%20CSS%20Grid%20instead); provide examples for responsive values.
- **Theming:** advise creating a custom theme with `createTheme` and providing it through `ThemeProvider`.
- **Common pitfalls:** emphasise checking MUI's official docs (v7) and not copying outdated examples; mention the migration from `GridLegacy` to the new `Grid` component.
- **Accessibility:** follow MUI's accessibility guidelines and add `aria` labels where appropriate.

